				If you are in a union, and are fired for no reason, then you stand a good chance to get your job back. My father made a living doing that. (getting peoples jobs back, not getting his job back after being fired) <br>  <br> If you are a CUSTOMER, and your service is terminated, you are out of luck. Where I work, I can say &quot;I'm sorry I dont feel like helping you right now.&quot; This may not be the best thing for the buisness, and my boss might not be happy, but he dosent care so I'm in the green. <br>  <br> Same thing applies here. They can provide as much or as little support as they feel like. There are no government laws stating how a buisness has to treat you. The only reason some buisnesses feel compelled to treat you well is its good for buisness. In an industry with few customers and lots of competition, buisnesses offer the best treatment they can. <br>  <br> In an industry with lots of customers and little competition, buisnesses can get away with anything. There are roughly 3 million people paying for EQ. Verant can piss a lot (several hundred) of people off and not feel the pinch... simply because they have a huge customer base, no competition, and have the best game in the industry.
